<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="29" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Dominican Minister of Foreign
                                    Affairs</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-01"><hi rend="italic">July 1,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The Dominican Government shares in your grief at the death of Secretary
                            Hay.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Minister
                            Sanchez.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>